Just like now, its the world against you, but what would have been so hard about posting your interest in doing VS?  Would it not make sense for people who are interested in doing something to be the people who make the initial move to get in on something?  You cant jump up and down and complain that you were not &quot;asked&quot; if you wanted to do something when noone has challenged the VS pickup slot before, if you do something and do it again and noone else expresses and interest in doing so, you'll prolly carry on doing it till someone says &quot;wait a mo, can I have a shot please?&quot;.  What the worst that can happen? You wait a month and CBA/VP do one more before its rotated?  I'm pretty sure that if a guild wanted to enter the rotation and they put their hand up wanting to go in it, they would not get the next VS pop, they'd get put at the end of the list so its just spread out and everyone gets their next one without being put back. <br>
