Ray <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utheodwynriddermark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheodwynRiddermark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/27/01 12:01:57 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://vivix.sysdudez.com/images/Theodwyn-thumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VS (Re: Sagemon)</span><hr size=1> I think what I'm seeing here is a communications SNAFU. It happens, and when it does, it needs to be cleared up and seen through if people wish to preserve their relationships. We share this server together, we've not had beef before, and so in my view we have a relationship that is in my mind worth defending.<br>
<br>
For whatever reason, and without blame, we had a communication mix-up. That mix-up proved to have consequences.<br>
<br>
There's no reason, in my mind, why good people can't get through something like this if they can find the medium and safety to communicate effectively.<br>
<br>
For better or worse, we're doing that here, in this thread, in this forum. So please folks, let's show what kind of people we are and wade through this and get some closure. Getting upset, no matter how valid our reasons are, just won't help.<br>
<br>
That said, let me take this space on your screen to focus on my view of where we're at here.<br>
<br>
Politics and diplomacy don't exist to serve their own ends. A lot of folks seem to lose sight of this. It's for bridging the gaps between people who don't see eye to eye.<br>
<br>
This is not a miscommunication between pick-up raiders. The miscommunication is between pick-up raid leaders. I'm sorry that pick-up raiders are watching it fly, as it were; but this is an opportunity to work it out and make it productive. Let's use it.<br>
<br>
Having a rotation of pick-up leaders to take turns for the VS pick-up slot may seem like porkbelly redundancy, but if it serves the purpose of keeping debate from happening, maybe it should be considered.<br>
<br>
Barring a rotation, I am hearing from Sagemon that a courtesy system between pick-up raid leaders would be useful (in his mind crucial) to preserving the spirit of the pick-up slot. Let me take a step back now. This is the first time that this issue has come to light, and I think we can all be forgiven for being a bit surprised by it and for finding ourselves unprepared for it.<br>
<br>
Now, let me address one of Sagemon's concerns<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> That begs the question: what do you consider to be the rules established by the community in securing a slot? Siilverain and some of your guildmates seem to believe either (1) that there are no rules, and that the pickup slot is FFA, or (2) that the proper way to obtain a slot is to ask Siilverain's permission. If CBA/VP is taking either of those positions, the system is not going to work.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
For better or for worse, the current rules for obtaining a slot on the rotation is to gather a raidforce and successfully bring down VS at a time in between the slots of the rotation guilds. Yes, this sparks the term &quot;KS&quot; and I find that personally distasteful. I'm banking on our credibility to avoid ruffling feathers, and my personal idea was to seek the permission of a rotation guild to gun for a slot when the time comes. By definition, that means in my mind that ganking the pick-up rotation is not an option, since there is no point of authority in the pick-up community to seek that permission from.<br>
<br>
Which is a very convenient segue to the second point: I have not and do not see Siilverain taking a position whereby her permission is needed to lead the pick-up slot. I simply am not seeing that, expressly or implied. We have a communication snafu, nothing more. I hope we can set that boundary and work inside it.<br>
<br>
At the same time, to continue on my point of personal character, I think we should also acknowledge that the pick-up rotation exists in no small part due to Siilverain's effort. This is my big point here in the face of mistrust. In my mind, Siilverain has earned that credibility many times over. She worked to secure the pick-up rotation, yet does not hold herself as lord/lady of it. This speaks volumes about her character as a person, and if anyone needs a reason to believe in the innocence and fair principles of her intentions, here it is.<br>
<br>
She didn't know that another pick-up leader wanted to lead VS. I believe that. I think there is reason why everyone else can too. If you can, then maybe you can have some faith that she had no intention of ganking anyone. And I promise you, when I did VS the last time around, I had no intention of ganking anyone either. And I honestly didn't know that anyone else wanted to do it. Siilverain asked if anyone wanted to do it, no one responded, she couldn't make it, I picked up the ball.<br>
<br>
Truth be told, I took leading VS as a duty, not as a particular pleasure. The VS battle has a very very very small sweet-spot, and if it comes off right, the whole affair seems simple and anti-climactic; and when it goes wrong it just all goes wrong and the raid party has to rez and rebuild each time. Not my particular idea of fun raid leading.<br>
<br>
I think we have a honest miscommunication here. The &quot;sideline noise&quot; is just that. Sideline noise. When parties square off in public, crowds gather, people talk. It happens.<br>
<br>
I have faith that if we can see this as an honest miscommunication, and move forward based on the issues raised, we can strike some kind of fair and equitable agreement.<br>
<br>
I am committed to doing whatever is best to preserve the spirit of the pick-up rotation, and will submit myself to either a rotation of the rotation, or a courtesy system, or whatever is decided upon as the most equitable solution.  Personally, I have no designs on leading VS unless the pick-up rotation is in danger of falling through.<br>
<br>
Striking that solution does require us to keep cool heads and work through it.<br>
<br>
I've served under several pick-up raid leaders, and had several of them on my raids as well. Fun times, good memories. I hope to have more of them. Let's not piss that away here.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
Théodwyn Riddermark, Disciple of Quellious (the Tranquil)<br>
Guild Leader, Vivix Protectorate<br>
